comments: Trap started.
Leaf diverter installed.
Trap moved ~2 ft towards near bank.
Added rocks to rear of pontoons to increase debris drum efficiency.
One half of the cone blocked with branches and filled with leaves; resulting in morts. Cone raised @ 9:30 due to rain; wind and weather forecast.
Debris drum stopped due to branches; trap full of leaves as result. Cleared trap; debris drum working again.
Mink got in to trap.
Mink was at screw trap again. Live trap was set on screw trap.
Strong wind blew all leaves off of trees; trap was 100% full. Morts.  Raised cone up on two blocks.
Leaf diverter removed.
Mink at screw trap again. Live trap re-baited.
Mink at screw trap again. Live trap re-baited with even more fish. Will install board tomorrow.
Trap stopped for holiday.
Caught and relocated mink.
Cone clogged with debris after rain event. Trap stopped for Thanksgiving holiday and winter tagging.
Fish present in livebox when we went to restart trap with one wsts mort.
Morts due to mink at trap.
Mink caught with live trap and relocated to Bear Cr.
End Early Migrant Season
Start Late Migrant Season
Hobo logger is missing.
Cone not spinning due to ice build-up. Live box ~25% ice. Trap stopped for coming cold weather.
Walkway added to trap!
Half of weir removed in preparation for hatchery releases. Additional block added to raise cone higher with lower water levels.
Rev counter not working.
Rev counter fixed. Stopped for 25H release.
Stopped for 11H force out
A couple limbs stuck in cone; trap was stopped upon arrival.
Increase in the proportion of healthy 25H fish.
Trap stopped for 11H force out
Trap stopped for coming rain event.
Trap moved ~5ft towards near bank
Trap interupted; stuck on ground; raised ~2in
Cone lowered ~3in
Log in cone.
Moved trap closer to near bank
Trap shut down for upcoming rain and Memorial Day weekend
End of Trapping Season
